<item>
            <title>[SPR-9221] Extend &lt;form:errors&gt; with something like errorElement</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-9221</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to add more flexibility to the &amp;lt;form:errors&amp;gt; tag.&lt;br/&gt;
E.g. to render something like&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;ul&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;li&amp;gt;error1&amp;lt;/li&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;li&amp;gt;error2&amp;lt;/li&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;ul&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With element=&quot;ul&quot; a part can be implemented but the &amp;lt;li&amp;gt; element is not possible.&lt;br/&gt;
The delimiter attribute just outputs it content after eacht error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe the &amp;lt;form:errors&amp;gt; tag can be extended with something like errorElement or itemElement indicating a wrapper element for the each error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Something like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;form:errors path=&quot;*&quot; element=&quot;ul&quot; errorElement=&quot;li&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
